## 💾 RAM - Short-Term Memory

### What is RAM?

**RAM (Random Access Memory)** is your computer's short-term memory. It's super fast but loses all data when you turn off your PC.

### Why is RAM Important?

```
RAM Speed Chart:
┌─────────────────────────────────────┐
│ Access Speed Comparison             │
├─────────────────────────────────────┤
│ Registers        1 nanosecond       │ ⚡⚡⚡⚡⚡
│ L1 Cache        ~4 nanoseconds      │ ⚡⚡⚡⚡
│ L2 Cache       ~10 nanoseconds      │ ⚡⚡⚡
│ L3 Cache       ~40 nanoseconds      │ ⚡⚡
│ RAM           ~100 nanoseconds      │ ⚡
│ SSD            ~10 microseconds     │ 🐢
│ HDD            ~10 milliseconds     │ 🐢🐢
└─────────────────────────────────────┘
```

### How RAM Works

```
┌──────────────────────────────────────────┐
│        RAM OPERATION FLOW                │
├──────────────────────────────────────────┤
│                                          │
│  1. You open a program                   │
│              │                           │
│              ▼                           │
│  2. OS loads program from HDD to RAM    │
│              │                           │
│              ▼                           │
│  3. CPU accesses program from RAM       │
│     (Much faster than HDD!)             │
│              │                           │
│              ▼                           │
│  4. Program runs smoothly                │
│              │                           │
│              ▼                           │
│  5. You close program                    │
│              │                           │
│              ▼                           │
│  6. RAM is freed (data erased)           │
│                                          │
│  💡 Key: RAM is VOLATILE (data lost     │
│     when power is off)                   │
│                                          │
└──────────────────────────────────────────┘
```

### RAM Types

| Type | Speed | Use | Year |
|------|-------|-----|------|
| **DDR4** | Up to 3200 MHz | Older laptops/PCs | 2014+ |
| **DDR5** | Up to 5600+ MHz | Modern systems | 2022+ |
| **LPDDR5** | Lower power | Smartphones | Recent |

