## 📊 Processor Generations & Evolution

### CPU Timeline

```
1971 - Intel 4004       ▓ (2,300 transistors)
  │
1978 - Intel 8086       ▓▓ (29,000 transistors) - PC era begins
  │
1989 - Intel i486       ▓▓▓ (1.2M transistors)
  │
2000 - Pentium 4        ▓▓▓▓ (42M transistors)
  │
2006 - Intel Core 2     ▓▓▓▓▓ (291M transistors)
  │
2010 - Intel i5/i7      ▓▓▓▓▓▓ (1.16B transistors)
  │
2017 - Intel i9         ▓▓▓▓▓▓▓ (4.2B transistors)
  │
2023 - Intel Raptor Lake ▓▓▓▓▓▓▓▓ (8B+ transistors)
  │
2024 - Modern CPUs      ▓▓▓▓▓▓▓▓▓ (50B+ transistors)

Moore's Law: Transistor count doubles ~every 2 years
